rComments: Prof Neville really cares about her students. She's accessible, explains her lectures well, and provides detailed feedback. Personally, I didn't find the course itself that interesting but that was on me. I didn't realize it was more of an environmental studies class than a usual pol course. Still, great prof. Work hard and you'll be ok

She genuinely cares about the learning of her students which comes through if you go to her office hours. Her lectures are organized with a focal point, and as long as you do your readings and attend lecture, you can do well. Sometimes the content got a bit dry, but overall, great prof.

Enviro governance from ground up should have been an interesting topic and prof Neville is very enthusiastic and passionate about the course but I didn't enjoy the course. I feel I didn't learn anything new and the lectures were often very slow. Could just be me...

Her syllabuses give a great indication as to what is expected on each assignment, she selects great readings and chooses lecture topics that are broad enough to stimulate discussion but with a key focus. She is very friendly and accessible outside of class, really cares about the topic she teaches and makes great efforts for her students experience
